The problem: Editing the SOAP API's IP whitelist in code ran clean through plan/apply, but the live resource policy in AWS never changed.
Root cause: The shared API Gateway module set the resource policy using the inline policy attribute on aws_api_gateway_rest_api. The AWS provider doesn't reliably detect drift on that inline attribute, so OpenTofu kept reporting "no changes" even when the IP list was different.
The fix I made: Changed the module to manage the policy through a dedicated aws_api_gateway_rest_api_policy resource, which diffs reliably. I gated it behind a new manage_policy_separately flag that defaults to false, so the existing hello API was completely unaffected — only the SOAP API opts in.
Scoped it safely: Turned the flag on only in the SOAP module call, confirmed via plan that the hello API showed no changes and only the SOAP policy migrated.
What slowed me down: I couldn't run locally (state backend returned 403), so I ran everything through GitHub Actions. I also temporarily forgot to actually add manage_policy_separately = true to soap_api.tf — once I added that line, the plan correctly showed the new policy resource being created with my IP.
Verified the fix: Applied it, confirmed the AWS console policy matched my code, then changed the IP again and saw a real diff in the plan — proving whitelist changes now apply every time.
